Subject: [RFC PATCH 0/9] m1n1: remaining T6040/J614s bring-up

This is a review-only draft of the remaining m1n1 changes used to boot a
MacBook Pro 14-inch M4 Pro (J614s, T6040 "Brava Chop") through kboot.

It is based on current upstream main at 7c7716b6, after:

  d3699d53 t6041: initial support
  0f221fc7 pcie: Add t8132/t6040 support

Those commits already provide the T6041 identity and the T6040 PCIe PHY
reset-bit change, so this series does not duplicate them.

Patches 1-8 contain the independently useful, hardware-verified pieces:

  - keep M4 secondaries out of state-losing WFI;
  - arm a bounded handoff watchdog;
  - gate DAPF instances which async-SError while retaining dart-mtp;
  - reuse the verified display carveout set;
  - describe the T6041 MCC layout and conservative T6040 cpufreq subset;
  - separate PMGR policy from ADT topology;
  - leave an upper guard page above the stage-2 log ring.

Patch 9 is deliberately RFC-only. Upstream now recognizes apcie,t6040,
but J614s also needs two T6040-only clock tunable windows and Apple's
PMGR gate ordering. The patch applies the complete live-proven clock
prefix and then stops. It does not enter the unresolved first PHY-IP
access (bring-up operation 115), initialize a port, or claim working
PCIe.

The branch was built twice from a clean tree on an arm64 Darwin host
with LLVM 22.1.8 and Rust nightly. Both builds produced:

  m1n1.bin
  SHA-256 f615a4ef538147cf434b32b851ebd39a00e0a3bbbc66df25feca2f97b2806f4b

  m1n1.elf
  SHA-256 f7d9150afb95314fdeb2610f08b5f0071990836b289704994b5f4ceefc5e3468

No image from this rebased series has been run on hardware. The
underlying changes cite their earlier bounded J614s validation, but the
series still needs normal review and a separately approved exact-image
test before use.

Excluded from this series are bring-up experiment helpers, DebugUSB PTY
transport, noninteractive linux.py policy, all tunable tracing, and the
unapproved operation-115 candidate. Those are host-tool work or
diagnostics rather than T6040 platform support.

Review questions:

  1. Should the handoff watchdog stay paired with the T6040 kboot change
     or be a separate opt-in policy?
  2. Is the per-SoC DAPF skip table acceptable until the missing hardware
     ownership signal is understood?
  3. Should patch 9 land as a safe incomplete prefix, or remain out of
     tree until the PHY-IP boundary and one port are complete?

CJ Damsleth (9):
  cpu: M4: park secondaries in WFE, WFI loses architectural state
  wdt: add wdt_arm_secs()
  dapf: gate DAPF init per SoC on the M4 generation
  kboot: t6040 display carveout reuse and M4 watchdog arm
  mcc: add t6041 (M4 Pro die) support
  cpufreq: minimal conservative t6040 support
  proxyclient: separate PMGR policy from ADT topology
  kboot: guard stage 2 log buffer at top of RAM
  pcie: prepare proven T6040 clock prefix

